Durban - The City has announced that Kenville Road will be closed to the public from 19 February, 2018 until 30 April, 2019. According to the City, this is being done accommodate the realignment of Inanda Road and the construction of a new bridge along Kenville Road. The affected portion of the road will be between Sea Cow Lake Road and 37 Kenville Road. The road will be closed permanently to the public during this time and will only be accessible to construction vehicles. However, the public will still be able to access a portion of Kenville Road through Smithfield and Kew roads. The City said services, including water, sewer, electricity, stormwater, Neotel and Telkom, may be affected as a result. POST